<description>

The Dashboard displays a personalized greeting at the top. The main content area contains two blocks side by side: the Timeline block and the Calendar block. The Timeline block aggregates upcoming teaching actions across all enrolled courses. It includes a time range dropdown (e.g., "Next 7 days"), a sort order dropdown, and a search field to find activities by name or type. When no items exist within the selected range, an empty state is shown. The Calendar block shows a monthly view with the current month and year as a heading. It includes an "All courses" dropdown to filter events by course, a "New event" button to create calendar entries, and left/right arrows to navigate between months. The current date is highlighted, and dates with events display their names inline. Two links at the bottom — "Full calendar" and "Import or export calendars" — open the dedicated calendar view and calendar data management respectively.

---


</description>

<workflows>
WF-001 | Select timeline time range | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Select time range: Next 7 days | on_success: Timeline refreshes to show items within selected range; if no items exist within the selected range, an empty state is shown.
WF-002 | Change timeline sort order | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Change sort order | on_success: Timeline is reordered according to the selected sort order.
WF-003 | Search the timeline | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Search timeline | on_success: Search results are shown in the timeline; if no items match the query, an empty-state is shown.
WF-004 | Filter calendar by course | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Filter by course | on_success: Calendar events are filtered to the selected course (or show all courses when 'All courses' is selected).
WF-005 | Navigate to previous month in calendar | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Previous month | on_success: Calendar updates to the previous month; event dates and current-date highlighting refresh to reflect the new month.
WF-006 | Navigate to next month in calendar | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Next month | on_success: Calendar updates to the next month; event dates and current-date highlighting refresh to reflect the new month.
WF-007 | Create a new calendar event | actor: Authenticated user | branch: user_logged_in == true | terminal: New event | on_success: opens calendar event creation flow
WF-008 | Open full calendar view | actor: Authenticated user | branch: user_logged_in == true | terminal: Full calendar | on_success: navigates to dedicated calendar view
WF-009 | Open calendar import/export management | actor: Authenticated user | branch: user_logged_in == true | terminal: Import or export calendars | on_success: opens calendar data management
</workflows>

